thread.title: Market's early gains evaporate

title: Market's early gains evaporate
text:
Fri, Aug 28, 2015, 12:30 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 30 mins Market's early gains evaporate Print 
The share market's strong early gains have evaporated as the financial and property sectors drop into the red. 
All four big banks opened higher on Friday, but with the exception of ANZ, had lost ground to be more than 0.5 per cent weaker at noon. 
Insurance and property stocks were also dragging on the market, almost offsetting the strong gains in mining and energy stocks caused by big rises in commodity prices, most notably oil. 
Woolworths was up 0.4 per cent after it reported a slide in annual profit and the departure of its chairman. 
KEY FACTS 
* At 1205 AEST, the benchmark S&P/ASX200 index was up 7.9 points, or 0.15 per cent, at 5241.2 points. 
* The broader All Ordinaries index was up 11.5 points, or 0.22 per cent, at 5254.1 points. 
* The September share price index futures contract was 29 points higher at 5,215 with 24,847 contracts traded at 1014 AEST.
